“All flesh is like grass, 
and all of man’s glory like the flower in the grass. 
The grass withers, and its flower falls;

Who, when he was cursed, didn’t curse back. 
When he suffered, didn’t threaten, 
but committed himself to him who judges righteously;

For you were going astray like sheep; 
but now have returned to the Shepherd 
and Overseer of your souls.

For the eyes of the Lord are on the righteous, 
and his ears open to their prayer; 
but the face of the Lord is against those who do evil.”
